      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">When you would cast a jutsu with more than one attack roll, the damage type becomes slashing and upon the conclusion of the jutsu, the target must make a Constitution saving throw with a penalty equal to the number of attacks they were hit by using your jutsu. On a failed saving throw, the creature gains ranks of bleeding equal to this penalty.</span></p>",
